<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920226-0061</DOCNO><DOCID>920226-0061.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Arnold Industries Inc.:   SilverEagle to Be Acquired   In Stock-Swap Transaction</HL><DATE>02/26/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4</SO><CO>   AIND</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)COMMERCIAL TRUCKING AND RELATED WAREHOUSING (TRK)</IN><NS>BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, REPURCHASES, SWAPS (BBK)ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>FLORIDA (FL)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PENNSYLVANIA (PA)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Arnold Industries Inc., Lebanon, Pa., said it tentativelyagreed to acquire closely held SilverEagle Transport Inc., aJacksonville, Fla., trucking concern, in a stock swap. Termsweren't disclosed.   An Arnold spokesman said completion of the transaction isexpected in late March, with the swap ratio based on anaverage closing price of Arnold's shares for five days priorto closing. New Arnold shares will be issued for the swap.</LP><TEXT>   Arnold, a trucking and warehousing company, said thatSilverEagle operates primarily as a truckload carrier alongthe Atlantic seaboard and in the South, and that it hadoperating revenue of more than $30 million in 1991. Atruckload carrier takes a full cargo from one point toanother, without any intervening pickups or drop-offs.   Arnold and SilverEagle's president, Stephen J. Silverman,said he has agreed to continue in that role after theacquisition.</TEXT></DOC>